Date: Fri, 8 Mar 1996 21:22:22 -0500 (EST)
From: Jamie Sheffield <jrsheffi@mailbox.syr.edu>
Only if they have bells surgically implanted!
Seriously though, I feel this is a worthwhile program, and can help go a
long way towards reducing the spread of disease among feral cats,
reducing the population boom of feral cats in many areas, and helping
homeworthy cats find homes (while preventing the destruction of animals
that can't help being successful breeders in our country). I would
defend this program as worthwhile in some areas (urban and suburban
centers) and would be more in favor of relocation and/or destruction of
the beasties in areas with ecosystems more likely to be adversely impacted
by their continued presence (rural, park, and forest areas). I would be
happy to discuss this topic further with interested parties on or off
the listserv.

Jamie Sheffield M.S.
jrsheffi@mailbox.syr.edu
http://members.aol.com/jamiesheff
